  "text": "Tree age and ring-width patterns were examined for all living A. mariesii trees (n ¼ 34) on the avalanche path by sampling stem cores at 30 to 50 cm in height, except for some larger trees (at 80-120 cm in height). We removed only one or two cores from each tree, since destructive sampling was restricted within the National Park. On the undisturbed forest, stem cores were sampled from some larger canopy trees (DBH . 30 cm, n ¼ 26) located on the northern half of the tree census area. For each core sample, the number of annual rings was counted, and annual ring-widths were measured using a microscope (0.01 mm in accuracy). Cross-dating was made visually using pointeryears, such as narrow rings or abrupt growth release [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
